# Reboot-Protocol
Reboot Protocol
by
Scopo Studios

Pitch:
A Sci-Fi Horror Game where players will navigate through a spaceship and fight an onslaught of monsters. They will need to find rare resources, manage their supplies, such as ammo and medical supplies, and solve various puzzles to escape the ship.

Setting:
The player will navigate through a Space Forest, a Spaceship (potentially different rooms in the spaceship), and an Alien planet.

Relationships
When the move buttons are pressed, the player’s character will be translated with the according speed towards the according position
When the attack button is pressed, if the player has a ranged weapon out, it will lower the ammo amount and damage enemies, if aimed at them.
When the attack button is pressed, if the player has a melee weapon out, it will damage enemies if they are in the hitbox of the attack
If the weapons damage the enemies when they are on low health, the enemies will disappear
If the inventory button is pressed, the inventory will open up, showing all the items the character has
When the AI-controlled enemies sense the player, the enemy will be translated with the according speed toward the player’s position
When the AI-controlled enemies are near the player’s position, the enemy will attack and damage the player, lowering the player’s health
If the interact button is pressed and the player is near an interactable environment, the environment’s world state will change accordingly (doors, lights, etc)
If the interact button is pressed, the player is near an interactable environment, and the player has an objective item, the environment’s world state will change accordingly (keys and locked doors, power battery and unpowered lights, etc)
If the interact button is pressed and the player is near a pick-up item, the item will disappear, and the item will show up in the player’s inventory
Game Mechanics:
In Reboot Protocol, players play as a Cadet navigating through an “alien” forest and entering a destroyed spaceship where the player needs to navigate their way out of it. The player controls the Cadet’s movement and the orientation of the character with WASD. The left mouse button will shoot, or use, the weapon the character is currently holding. If the hitbox of the attack hits any enemies, this will lower their health or eliminate them if they are in a low amount of health. The E button will interact with objects or the environment around them. Interaction with objects will involve picking up either ammo for various weapons, health items, or objective items. Interaction with the environment will involve changing world states, such as opening doors, opening chests, or turning on lights and giving user information on specific items.
